{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<h2>What is danger.js anyway?</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/\">DangerJS</a> runs during your CI process, and helps your team to automate certain manual code review tasks like:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Is there a <code class=\"language-text\">new library</code> or <code class=\"language-text\">module installed</code>?</li>\n<li>Does this <code class=\"language-text\">PR changes</code> are added to <code class=\"language-text\">changelog file</code>?</li>\n<li>Is <code class=\"language-text\">.lockfile</code> kept up to date?</li>\n<li>Will this change <code class=\"language-text\">increase my bundle size</code>?</li>\n<li>So on and on.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<center>\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 39.22222222222222%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"DangerJS in React\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-fb8a0.png\" srcset=\"/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-526de.png 885w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-08f6a.png 1770w,\n/static/github.com_facebook_react_pull_13695-d181b4ebafb44ae9f94b25e7b3aecf17-029df.png 1800w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <i class=\"m-top-15\">React using danger.js</i>\n</center>\n<h4>Integrating Danger.js in Github &#x26; Travis</h4>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10\">Step 1:</b> Add <code class=\"language-text\">dangerjs</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">your devDependencies</code> in package.json file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">yarn add danger -D</code></pre></div>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10\">Step 2:</b> Create <code class=\"language-text\">dangerfile.js</code> file in your project.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token comment\">// Import the feedback functions</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> message<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> warn<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> fail<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> markdown <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">\"danger\"</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Add a message to the table</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">message</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"You have added 2 more modules to the app\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">//  Adds a warning to the table</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">warn</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"You have not included a CHANGELOG entry.\"</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Declares a blocking</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">fail</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token template-string\"><span class=\"token string\">`ESLint has failed with </span><span class=\"token interpolation\"><span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">${</span>fails<span class=\"token interpolation-punctuation punctuation\">}</span></span><span class=\"token string\"> fails.`</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n\n<span class=\"token comment\">// Show markdown under the table:</span>\n<span class=\"token function\">markdown</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">\"## New module Danger\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">+</span> dangerYarnInfo<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10\">Step 3 (Optional):</b> Create an <code class=\"language-text\">github account</code> for <code class=\"language-text\">your bot</code>.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10\">Step 4:</b> Create a <a href=\"https://github.com/settings/tokens/new\">New personal access token</a> in <code class=\"language-text\">github</code> for <code class=\"language-text\">read &amp; write</code> access for your bot.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<center>\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 57.14285714285714%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"Github Settings Page\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-fb8a0.png\" srcset=\"/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-526de.png 885w,\n/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/github-token-5eff0cafb42ebce2e00f0fd224ec1e49-ba3b9.png 1498w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <i class=\"m-top-15\">Github Settings Page</i>\n</center>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-10\">Step 5 (Final Step):</b> <code class=\"language-text\">Hooking danger.js</code> in <a href=\"https://travis-ci.org/\">Travis CI</a></p>\n<ul class=\"m-left-10\">\n  <li>Copy the <b>generated personal token</b> from your github or your bot account you created.</li>\n  <li>Go to your <b>project settings</b> in <b>Travis CI</b>.</li>\n  <li>Create a <b>new environment variable</b> called <b>DANGER_GITHUB_API_TOKEN</b> and the value is <b>your personal token</b>.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b></p>\n<center>\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 49.73890339425588%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"Travis Settings Page\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-fb8a0.png\" srcset=\"/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-526de.png 885w,\n/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/travis-ci.org-00330b45b1127e03029f6669232485ed-78ae1.png 1532w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <i class=\"m-top-15\">Travis Settings Page</i>\n</center>\n<p>After this step, you should be seeing <code class=\"language-text\">bot</code> account adding <code class=\"language-text\">comments</code> to your every PR as per your <code class=\"language-text\">dangerfile.js</code> config.</p>\n<p><b class=\"m-left-20\">Example:</b> <a href=\"https://github.com/code-kotis/barcode-scanner/pull/57\" target=\"_blank\">QR Code Scanner</a></p>\n<center>\n  \n  <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 105%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\">\n      <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\" alt=\"Code Kotis - QR Code Scanner\" title=\"\" src=\"/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-fb8a0.png\" srcset=\"/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-1a291.png 148w,\n/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-2bc4a.png 295w,\n/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-fb8a0.png 590w,\n/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-526de.png 885w,\n/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-fa2eb.png 1180w,\n/static/github.com_code-kotis-f72dff81ecb7b2b952e1601f311a8c12-4f5a6.png 1400w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\">\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  <i class=\"m-top-15\"><a href=\"qrcodescan.in\" target=\"_blank\">QR Code Scanner</a></i>\n</center>\n<h5>Hot Tips:</h5>\n<p>You can test your changes locally using following terminal command.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"shell\"><pre class=\"language-shell\"><code class=\"language-shell\">yarn danger <span class=\"token function\">pr</span> <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>your-pr-link<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h5>References:</h5>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/11865/files\">ReactJS</a> dangerfile.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/tutorials.html\">Tutorials</a> for other app such as node app, node libraries etc.</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://danger.systems/js/guides/getting_started.html#setting-up-danger-to-run-on-your-ci\">More tutorials</a> on adding danger.js to other CI’s</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Thank you for reading my post till the end. If you like my post <code class=\"language-text\">share it</code> 😇.</p>","frontmatter":{"date":"October 17, 2018","path":"/blog/2018/add-dangerjs-to-your-project","title":"Add danger.js to your OSS in 5 mins"}}},"pageContext":{}}